THOUGHT: The crash arises when VectorCombine::foldShuffleOfSelects calls TTI getShuffleCost with a mask containing indices that are out-of-bounds for the concatenated source vectors. A robust fix is to add an early guard in foldShuffleOfSelects to validate the mask against the shuffle operand element count before any TTI queries. I will insert a check right after obtaining the destination vector type: derive the operand vector element count from I.getOperand(0) (the first select feeding the shuffle), and bail out if any mask element is not -1 and is >= 2 * NumOpElts.

```bash
sed -i '2041i\  auto *Op0VecTy = dyn_cast<FixedVectorType>(I.getOperand(0)->getType());
  if (!Op0VecTy)
    return false;
  unsigned NumOpElts = Op0VecTy->getNumElements();
  if (!llvm::all_of(Mask, [NumOpElts](int M) { return M == -1 || (M >= 0 && M < (int)(NumOpElts * 2)); }))
    return false;' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VectorCombine.cpp && /llvm-autofix/build/llvm-build/130250/bin/opt /tmp/test.ll -passes=vector-combine -S -mtriple=x86_64-- -mcpu=x86-64-v2
```

